<label class="arcana-unlock-label" for="ma11_unlocked">Unlocked</label>
        <div class="arcana-front">
          <p>A pair of wooden figurines, carved from blackwood and worn smooth with age and use. A whitish shaft has been driven into the top of each figurine's head, and the eyes and forehead of each are stained a rusty, reddish color. The figurines resist all mundane attempts to damage them.</p>
          <p>When you mark a figurine's eyes with blood and likewise mark your own eyelids, you see through the eyes of the figurine whenever you close your eyes, for as long as the blood remains. When you anoint a figurine with your own blood and then sleep in its presence, roll +CON: on a 10+, you dream lucidly of the spirit in the figurine — it might be persuaded to reveal its name, or the name of its fellow spirit, or the method of calling them forth; on a 7-9, you dream of the spirit, but the dream is fleeting, strange, and disorienting.</p>
