          <p>When you open the box and speak the name of a creature type or a specific individual, release the plague wind, and then re-seal the box, roll +CON: on a 10+, the plague wind seeks only your named target(s) and returns to the box when done; on a 7-9, the wind finds its target(s) but also touches 1d4 others nearby (GM's choice). On a 6-, the wind escapes before you can re-seal the box and touches everything living in the area before you can recapture it.</p>
          <p>Those touched by the plague wind become lethargic, feverish, and weak. They mark all three debilities and cannot clear them until they rest completely for two weeks. Creatures of unusual hardiness may resist; roll +CON vs your roll to release the wind. If a creature touched by the plague wind is already sick or debilitated, they risk death.</p>
