          <div class="arcana-requirements">
            <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_mn62_req1" value="1"> …determine what the pot originally contained and how it was made.</label>
            <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_mn62_req2" value="1"> …acquire and prepare the same ingredients (Value 1, slow).</label>
            <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_mn62_req3" value="1"> …test the preparation on yourself and survive the consequences.</label>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="arcana-back">
          <p class="arcana-back-heading">Smoke of Forgetting</p>
          <p><em>Uses: </em><input type="number" name="attr_mn62_uses" value="0" style="width:44px"></p>
          <p>When you prepare a batch of the smoke (Value 1, slow), gain 1d4+1 uses. When you break a sealed container of the smoke in an enclosed space or in a target's face, all who breathe the smoke must roll +CON: on a 10+, they remember nothing from the last hour; on a 7-9, they remember fragments — impressions, emotions, no specifics; on a 6-, they remember everything clearly. You are immune to your own smoke. The smoke dissipates in about a minute in open air; in a closed room, it lingers for several minutes. Objects cannot be made to "forget" but anyone who witnessed their handling will not recall doing so.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
