        <label class="arcana-unlock-label" for="mn63_unlocked">Unlocked</label>
        <div class="arcana-front">
          <p>A fist-sized chunk of grey-green stone, warm to the touch. It hums at a frequency just below hearing. It is not a rock — it responds differently to pressure at different points, as if something inside is shifting. When you hold it and listen carefully, you sometimes hear a low resonant tone that seems to have structure, rhythm, intention. To unlock its mysteries, you must…</p>
          <p class="arcana-req-heading">Requirements — mark when complete:</p>
          <div class="arcana-requirements">
            <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_mn63_req1" value="1"> …learn to recognize the stone's language (weeks of careful listening and experimentation).</label>
            <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_mn63_req2" value="1"> …respond to it in kind, matching its resonance with your voice or touch.</label>
            <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_mn63_req3" value="1"> …ask it a question it is willing to answer, and understand the reply.</label>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="arcana-back">
          <p class="arcana-back-heading">Stonespeaker</p>
          <p>When you hold the living stone against any natural stone surface and listen, you can ask the stone one of the following and receive an honest, if slow and literal, answer: What has passed here recently? / What lies beyond this stone (describe up to 50 feet)? / What is this stone's greatest point of weakness? / Is there something alive or dead within or beneath this stone? When you ask a question of the stone about the deep past — centuries or more ago — you have advantage on the roll. On a 6- on any roll involving the living stone, it goes dormant until you spend a week in close contact with it, coaxing it back.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
