          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="arcana-back">
          <p class="arcana-back-heading">Crow Tongue</p>
          <p>You can speak with crows and understand them. They are not loyal or friendly, but they are curious and mercenary. When you offer a crow something it values (bright objects, scraps of meat, interesting things) and ask it a question about what it has seen, roll +CHA: on a 10+, it tells you clearly and in detail; on a 7-9, it tells you, but the information is partial, jumbled with irrelevancies, or comes at an additional price; on a 6-, it takes your offering and tells you nothing useful, or something actively misleading. Crows remember faces. If you have cheated, harmed, or disrespected a crow before, you have disadvantage on all rolls to deal with crows until you make meaningful amends. When you call out to all crows within hearing and ask them to carry a message, they will — eventually, and in their own fashion.</p>
